The paper deals with joint detection of co-channel signals, which is a common problem in wireless communication systems. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of factor graphs, which are commonly used in Statistical Learning (cs.LG) and Signal Processing (cs.SI) applications. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of multiple antennas, which is a common topic in Multimedia (cs.MM) applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT and cs.NI, followed by cs.SI, cs.LG, and cs.MM.
